    "id": "scenario_7",
    "title": "Plugin Server Compromise — Malicious Plugin Execution",
    "description": "An attacker uploads a malicious plugin to PostHog's plugin server (Node.js process). The Pino-based logs reveal the attack: a plugin installation from an untrusted source, the plugin executing unauthorized network calls (data exfiltration), accessing environment variables (credential theft), and consuming excessive resources (crypto mining or DoS). The plugin server's structured JSON logs capture the full attack chain.",
